What does this code do?

```javascript
let input = document.getElementById('search');
let counter = document.getElementById('char-count');

input.addEventListener('input', function() {
  counter.textContent = input.value.length + ' characters';
});
```

A toggle button should show and hide a sidebar. It works the first time (sidebar appears), but clicking again does nothing. Which code has this problem?

```javascript
let sidebar = document.getElementById('sidebar');
let toggleBtn = document.getElementById('toggle');

toggleBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {
  sidebar.style.display = 'block';
});
```
